      "rationale": "OpenFOAM v9 is maintained under Git version control with tagged releases. The CFD team executed the standard regression suite (212 tests, 0 failures) prior to study commencement. Release notes confirm no breaking changes to incompressible flow or scalar transport solvers between v8 and v9."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions demonstrates second-order spatial convergence for velocity and scalar fields.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification confirmed second-order convergence in L2 norm for velocity (observed order 1.97) and hemolysis scalar (observed order 1.94) on three systematically refined grids. Residuals converge to < 1e-6 in all cases."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on fine mesh for scalar shear stress and RH index at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "GCI computed per Celik et al. (2008) protocol. Maximum GCI across all operating points and QoIs is 2.3% (shear stress, 3 L/min, 2000 RPM). All other GCI values < 1.8%. Fine mesh of 14.8M cells selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid properties, flow rates, rotational speeds, temperature) documented and match CFD boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted with porcine blood (hematocrit 33 ± 2%, viscosity 3.2 ± 0.3 mPa·s at 37°C). Flow rates controlled to ± 0.05 L/min, rotational speed to ± 10 RPM. CFD boundary conditions set to nominal experimental values; sensitivity to fluid property uncertainty assessed via ± 10% viscosity sweep."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mean absolute error in RH index < 0.15 across all 5 operating points; Pearson correlation coefficient > 0.90.",
      "rationale": "MAE = 0.07, Pearson r = 0.94 across 5 operating points. CFD correctly rank-orders all 5 operating conditions by hemolysis severity. Worst-case operating point (6 L/min, 3500 RPM) identified consistently in both CFD and experiment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (RH index, scalar shear stress distribution) are directly relevant to the hemolysis acceptance criterion and regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which is the direct input to the predicate device comparison criterion (RH < 1). Secondary QoI is volume-averaged scalar shear stress, which governs the power-law damage model. Both QoIs are mechanistically linked to the clinical endpoint of haemolysis-induced anaemia."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
